//Instruction experience blocks:

<page startingexp_exp>
In the next task you will see customer ratings for a restaurant, one at a time. Each rating is on a scale from 0 (worst) to 10 (best).
~nPlease pay close attention to the ratings as they appear. Occasionally we will check your attention by asking what the immediately preceding rating was.
</page>

<page startingexp_desc>
In the next task you will see customer ratings for a football player, one at a time. Each rating is on a scale from 0 (worst) to 5 (best).
~nAs the ratings accumulate, a histogram on the left side of the screen will show how many times each rating value has been given so far.
~nPlease pay close attention. Occasionally we will check your attention by asking what the immediately preceding rating was.
</page>

<page startingexp_both>
In the next task you will see customer ratings for a restaurant, one at a time. Each rating is on a scale from 0 (worst) to 10 (best).
~nAs the ratings accumulate, a histogram on the left side of the screen will show how many times each rating value has been given so far.
~nPlease pay close attention to both the individual ratings and the histogram. Occasionally we will check your attention by asking what the immediately preceding rating was.
</page>


